<paragraph blockId="1.[151,616,1040,1103]" box="[151,274,1076,1103]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,265,1076,1103]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,250,1855,1879]" captionStartId-2="3.[151,250,829,853]" captionTargetBox-0="[152,1435,184,1276]" captionTargetBox-1="[164,1423,1421,1830]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,182,805]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@2.[151,1436,181,1276]" captionTargetId-1="figure-65@2.[164,1423,1420,1830]" captionTargetId-2="figure-27@3.[151,1436,181,805]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionTargetPageId-2="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (male). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. head, frontal view; E. vertex of head, showing conical tubercles; F. hind tarsus, lateral view; G. epiproct, dorsal view; H. paraproct, lateral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Male genitalia of Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov.. A. genitalia, dorsal view; B. genitalia, ventral view." captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (female). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. ovipositor, lateral view; E. subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641473" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641475" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641477" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6641473/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6641475/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6641477/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1148,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1148,1174]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body medium sized (
<figureCitation box="[619,754,1148,1175]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,184,1276]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,181,1276]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (male). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. head, frontal view; E. vertex of head, showing conical tubercles; F. hind tarsus, lateral view; G. epiproct, dorsal view; H. paraproct, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641473/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Figs. 1A–C</figureCitation>
). Vertex of head divided into two conical tubercles, bases of the well-developed tubercles slightly drawn together, obtusely rounded apices obviously separated (
<figureCitation box="[1288,1424,1184,1211]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,184,1276]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,181,1276]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (male). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. head, frontal view; E. vertex of head, showing conical tubercles; F. hind tarsus, lateral view; G. epiproct, dorsal view; H. paraproct, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641473/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Figs. 1D, E</figureCitation>
). Eyes oval, protruding forward (
<figureCitation box="[500,630,1220,1247]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,184,1276]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,181,1276]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (male). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. head, frontal view; E. vertex of head, showing conical tubercles; F. hind tarsus, lateral view; G. epiproct, dorsal view; H. paraproct, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641473/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Figs. 1D, E</figureCitation>
). Anterior margin of pronotum straight, posterior margin protruding caudad, ventral margin arc-shaped; posterior margin of mesonotum protruding caudad; posterior margin of metanotum slightly protruding caudad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1148,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">
Legs long and slender. Fore femur about 1.6 times longer than the pronotum, ventrally unarmed, internal genicular lobe with 1 small spine, external genicular lobe with 1 long spine; fore tibia ventrally with 2 inner spines and 2 outer spines, apex with 1 pair of small spines on dorsal surface and 1 pair of long spines on ventral surface, between the paired ventral spines with 1 small spine. Middle femur ventrally unarmed, internal and external genicular lobes with 1 long spine respectively; middle tibiae ventrally with 1–2 inner spines and 1 outer spine, apex with 1 pair of small spines on dorsal surface and 1 pair of long spines on ventral surface, between the paired ventral spines with 1 small spine. Hind femur ventrally with 5–8 inner spines and without outer spine; hind tibia dorsally with 59–62 inner spines and 59–68 outer spines, arrange in groups, ventral and dorsal surface with a pair of small sub-apical spines respectively, apex with 1 pair of long dorsal spines and 1 pair of long ventral spines; the longest dorso-apical spine reaching the apex of the dorso-apical spine of hind metatarsus (
<figureCitation box="[927,1011,1652,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,184,1276]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,181,1276]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (male). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. head, frontal view; E. vertex of head, showing conical tubercles; F. hind tarsus, lateral view; G. epiproct, dorsal view; H. paraproct, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641473/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Hind metatarsus keeled beneath.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1148,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">
Well-developed epiproct extending backwards and nearly rectangular, posterior margin of epiproct rounded (
<figureCitation box="[160,252,1724,1751]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,184,1276]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,181,1276]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (male). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. head, frontal view; E. vertex of head, showing conical tubercles; F. hind tarsus, lateral view; G. epiproct, dorsal view; H. paraproct, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641473/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
). Paraproct shorter than epiproct (
<figureCitation box="[652,745,1724,1751]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,184,1276]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,181,1276]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (male). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. head, frontal view; E. vertex of head, showing conical tubercles; F. hind tarsus, lateral view; G. epiproct, dorsal view; H. paraproct, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641473/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). Dorsolateral lobes of male genitalia distinctly sclerotized, basal part with a large projection; apex of median lobe with 1 pair of dorsal lobules and 2 pairs of ventral lobules; epiphallus of male genitalia like the shape of ligule-like, rather small (
<figureCitation box="[946,1080,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1855,1879]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,1421,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-65@2.[164,1423,1420,1830]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male genitalia of Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov.. A. genitalia, dorsal view; B. genitalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641475" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641475/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Figs. 2A, B</figureCitation>
). Male subgenital plate bilobed in the apical area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1148,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1869,1895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Female.</emphasis>
General appearance similar to that of male (
<figureCitation box="[784,918,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,829,853]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,805]" captionTargetId="figure-27@3.[151,1436,181,805]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (female). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. ovipositor, lateral view; E. subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641477/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Figs. 3A–C</figureCitation>
), but the fore femur of some female specimens ventrally with 1 spine, and hind femur ventrally with 7–8 inner spines. Ovipositor about half the length of hind femur; base of ovipositor broad, narrowing to apex; apex pointed and slightly curved upwards; almost indistinct denticles on ventral edge of distal part of inferior valves (
<figureCitation box="[813,905,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,829,853]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,805]" captionTargetId="figure-27@3.[151,1436,181,805]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (female). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. ovipositor, lateral view; E. subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641477/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate nearly triangular and with a projection in the middle part of hind margin (
<figureCitation box="[658,745,2012,2039]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,829,853]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,805]" captionTargetId="figure-27@3.[151,1436,181,805]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Megatachycines rectangularis sp. nov. (female). A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, lateral view; C. habitus, ventral view; D. ovipositor, lateral view; E. subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641477/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
