<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="249" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,935,1430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1223,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="249">Discussion.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Qin, Liu &amp; Li, 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Qin, Liu &amp; Li" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[675,1223,1223,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Megatachycines" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis box="[675,973,1223,1249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="249">Megatachycines elongatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Qin, Y. Y. &amp; Liu, X. W. &amp; Li, K." box="[988,1216,1223,1250]" pageId="3" pageNumber="249" pagination="596 - 600" refId="ref2208" refString="Qin, Y. Y., Liu, X. W. &amp; Li, K. (2017) Review of the genus Microtachycines Gorochov with two new species (Orthoptera, Rhaphidophoridae, Aemodogryllinae) from China. Zootaxa, 4216 (6), 596 - 600. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4216.6.6" type="journal article" year="2017">Qin, Liu &amp; Li, 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the morphology of the lateral lobes of male genitalia, but can be distinguished from the latter in several respects. First, the shape of the epiproct of male and the shape of the subgenital plate of female are different between these two species. Second, the number of spines on the hind tibiae of this new species is slightly lower than that in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Qin, Liu &amp; Li, 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Qin, Liu &amp; Li" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Megatachycines" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1436,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="249">Megatachycines elongatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Qin, Y. Y. &amp; Liu, X. W. &amp; Li, K." box="[159,391,1367,1394]" pageId="3" pageNumber="249" pagination="596 - 600" refId="ref2208" refString="Qin, Y. Y., Liu, X. W. &amp; Li, K. (2017) Review of the genus Microtachycines Gorochov with two new species (Orthoptera, Rhaphidophoridae, Aemodogryllinae) from China. Zootaxa, 4216 (6), 596 - 600. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4216.6.6" type="journal article" year="2017">Qin, Liu &amp; Li, 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Third, the coloration of the body is obviously different between the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1115,1403,1430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="249" type="etymology">
